title: How to stop Europe’s space sector from lagging behind in defense
summary: Europe has power, influence and a huge economy — so why is it lagging behind in defense?

title: GAO report warns Artemis 3 landing may be delayed to 2027
summary: The first crewed landing of NASA’s Artemis lunar exploration effort is unlikely to happen before 2027, a report by the Government Accountability Office concluded.

title: NASA researchers get permission to apply for China’s moon samples
summary: NASA-funded researchers have been granted permission to apply for access to China's Chang'e-5 lunar samples in an exception to a prohibition on bilateral activities.

title: SpaceX Starship, Axiom Spacesuit Delays Likely To Push 2025 Artemis III to 2027 Says NASA GAO Report
summary: NASA is gearing to land humans on the moon for the first time since 1972 under the Artemis program; however, a recent report by the GAO reveals significant challenges that may impede the planned Artemis III crewed lunar landing in 2025.

title: Australian startup develops dual-headed space camera
summary: Infinity Avionics is working with the University of New South Wales Canberra Space and Australian startup Nominal Systems to develop technology to autonomously detect space objects.

title: Intelsat to bring multi-orbit Wi-Fi to regional American Airlines jets
summary: American Airlines announced plans Nov. 30 to equip nearly 500 regional jets with multi-orbit Wi-Fi connectivity from Intelsat over two years starting in early 2024.

title: Ursa Major closes $138 million Series D and D-1 financings
summary: Rocket propulsion startup Ursa Major announced Nov. 30 it has raised $138 million in Series D and D-1 funding rounds.

title: Intelsat steps up partnership with SpaceX in multi-orbit antenna
summary: Intelsat is producing a new flat panel antenna that enables moving vehicles to use broadband services from the company’s geostationary satellites and from SpaceX’s Starlink network

title: Blue Origin nearing New Glenn milestones ahead of debut flight
summary: As 2023 nears its close, there has been a large increase in publicly visible movement from Blue Origin around its Kennedy Space Center and Cape Canaveral facilities. With sightings of New Glenn booster segments, upper-stage tank sections, payload fairings, and new support hardware arriving at Port Canaveral, it seems Blue Origin is pushing to hit major milestones in 2024.
